cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.SC

The paper deals with the problem of realizing geometric permutations of disjoint convex sets in $\mathbb{R}^3$, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an effective algorithm for a combinatorial problem related to the main problem, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions gaining new insights into the structure of geometric permutations, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
